{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VBPSnen7aTcxMgqh66so3k","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me also check if webpack's yarn.lock resolves to 4.17.21.\n\nActually I already saw that in the webpack yarn.lock:\n```\nlodash@^4.17.15, lodash@^4.17.19, lodash@^4.17.21, lodash@^4.17.4, lodash@^4.7.0:\n  version \"4.17.21\"\n```\n\nAnd for jest yarn.lock:\n```\n\"lodash@npm:^4.15.0, lodash@npm:^4.17.15, lodash@npm:^4.17.19, lodash@npm:^4.17.20, lodash@npm:^4.17.21, lodash@npm:^4.17.4, lodash@npm:~4.17.15\":\n  resolution: \"lodash@npm:4.17.21\"\n```\n\nSo all lodash consumers in jest and webpack resolve to 4.17.21, which is safe. But the lodash repo itself is version 4.17.20 (vulnerable), and its devDependency uses 4.17.14. Let me double-check the webpack yarn.lock to make sure I'm reading the lodash version resolution correctly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1748,"cache_read_input_tokens":35716,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1748,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"574eed9d-a223-4c19-b8bf-209e9b77cb51","uuid":"40dd94ea-39ab-477a-9077-b50d8a6960f2"}
