{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013FZzhobxHHrpKmX7SYSajf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XnLkHGsGvSzawdTZTMPa5u","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/BLAST_RADIUS.md","content":"# CVE-2021-23337 Blast Radius Analysis\n\n## 1. CVE Identification\n\n| Field | Detail |\n|-------|--------|\n| **CVE ID** | CVE-2021-23337 |\n| **Package** | lodash (npm) |\n| **Vulnerable Range** | < 4.17.21 |\n| **Fixed Version** | 4.17.21 |\n| **Severity** | High (CVSS 7.2) |\n| **Type** | Command Injection |\n| **Vector** | `_.template` function — the `sourceURL` option is not sanitized, allowing injection of arbitrary code when user-controlled content reaches the template engine options |\n\nThe vulnerability is in `lodash`'s `_.template` function. When `sourceURL` (or `variable`) options contain user-controlled input, it is passed directly into a `Function()` constructor, enabling OS-level command injection in Node.js environments.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Direct Dependents\n\nThree manifest files in the workspace directly declare `lodash` as a dependency:\n\n### `/workspace/lodash/package.json`\n- **Type**: The lodash package itself\n- **Version (the package)**: `4.17.20` — **VULNERABLE**\n- **devDependency declared**: `\"lodash\": \"4.17.14\"` (pinned) — **VULNERABLE**\n\n### `/workspace/webpack/package.json`\n- **Type**: `devDependency`\n- **Declared range**: `^4.17.19`\n- **Resolved version (yarn.lock)**: `4.17.21` — **SAFE**\n\n### `/workspace/jest/examples/manual-mocks/package.json`\n- **Type**: `dependency`\n- **Declared range**: `^4.17.19`\n- **Resolved version (yarn.lock)**: `4.17.21` — **SAFE**\n\n---\n\n## 3. Transitive Dependency Paths\n\n### 3a. lodash repo (`/workspace/lodash/package-lock.json`)\n\nAll transitive consumers resolve to **4.17.14** — **ALL VULNERABLE**:\n\n| Package | Requires | Resolved |\n|---------|----------|----------|\n| `async` | `^4.17.14` | `4.17.14` |\n| `babel-core` | `^4.17.4` | `4.17.14` |\n| `babel-generator` | `^4.17.4` | `4.17.14` |\n| `babel-helper-define-map` | `^4.17.4` | `4.17.14` |\n| `babel-helper-regex` | `^4.17.4` | `4.17.14` |\n| `babel-plugin-transform-es2015-block-scoping` | `^4.17.4` | `4.17.14` |\n| `babel-register` | `^4.17.4` | `4.17.14` |\n| `babel-template` | `^4.17.4` | `4.17.14` |\n| `babel-traverse` | `^4.17.4` | `4.17.14` |\n| `babel-types` | `^4.17.4` | `4.17.14` |\n| `benchmark` | `^4.17.4` | `4.17.14` |\n| `docdown` | `^4.17.5` | `4.17.14` |\n| `lodash-doc-globals` | `^4.16.0` | `4.17.14` |\n\n**Example 2-hop chain**: `lodash (repo)` → devDependency `babel-core` → `lodash@4.17.14`\n\n### 3b. jest repo (`/workspace/jest/yarn.lock`)\n\nAll transitive consumers resolve to **4.17.21** — **ALL SAFE**:\n\n| Package | Requires | Resolved |\n|---------|----------|----------|\n| `@babel/core@7.12.9` | `^4.17.19` | `4.17.21` |\n| `@docusaurus/core` | `^4.17.21` | `4.17.21` |\n| `@docusaurus/plugin-client-redirects` | `^4.17.21` | `4.17.21` |\n| `@docusaurus/plugin-content-blog` | `^4.17.21` | `4.17.21` |\n| `@docusaurus/plugin-content-docs` | `^4.17.21` | `4.17.21` |\n| `@docusaurus/theme-classic` | `^4.17.21` | `4.17.21` |\n| `@docusaurus/theme-search-algolia` | `^4.17.21` | `4.17.21` |\n| `@docusaurus/utils` | `^4.17.21` | `4.17.21` |\n| `@microsoft/api-extractor` | `~4.17.15` | `4.17.21` |\n| `@react-native-community/cli` | `^4.17.15` | `4.17.21` |\n| `@react-native-community/cli-platform-android` | `^4.17.15` | `4.17.21` |\n| `@react-native-community/cli-platform-ios` | `^4.17.15` | `4.17.21` |\n| `@react-native-community/cli-tools` | `^4.17.15` | `4.17.21` |\n| `benchmark` | `^4.17.4` | `4.17.21` |\n| `cheerio` | `^4.15.0` | `4.17.21` |\n| `conventional-changelog-core` | `^4.17.15` | `4.17.21` |\n| `conventional-changelog-writer` | `^4.17.15` | `4.17.21` |\n| `conventional-commits-parser` | `^4.17.15` | `4.17.21` |\n| `example-manual-mocks` | `^4.17.19` | `4.17.21` |\n| `git-raw-commits` | `^4.17.