21` | no |\n| `jest` | `example-manual-mocks` (direct dep) | `^4.17.19` | `4.17.21` | no |\n| `jest` | `@babel/core@7.12.9` (transitive) | `^4.17.19` | `4.17.21` | no |\n| `jest` | `@docusaurus/*` (transitive) | `^4.17.21` | `4.17.21` | no |\n\n### Key Findings\n\n- **The `lodash` repository itself** is the primary exposure: it contains lodash at version `4.17.20` and its entire devDependency tree pins or resolves to `4.17.14` — both below the fix threshold of `4.17.21`.\n- **webpack** and **jest** both resolve lodash to `4.17.21` (patched) in their lock files, including all transitive consumers. No exposure in those repos.\n- Remediation: upgrade the lodash repo's own version to `4.17.21` and update the `package.json` devDependency from the pinned `4.17.14` to `^4.17.21`.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1496,"cache_read_input_tokens":38631,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1496,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":40,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"574eed9d-a223-4c19-b8bf-209e9b77cb51","uuid":"b0aaf2ea-ec5e-454f-958f-85d6f22f550b"}
